This is the archived version of the repository service support website created and maintained from 2006 until 2013. It was superseded by a revised version in July 2013. </description> <dc:date>2013-01-01T00:00:00Z</dc:date> </item> <item rdf:about="http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/202016"> <title>DSpace@Cambridge Implementation Project website</title> <link>http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/202016</link> <description>DSpace@Cambridge Implementation Project website Morgan, Peter; Massiou, Anna DSpace@Cambridge is the Institutional Repository of the University of Cambridge. It received its original project funding from the Cambridge-MIT Institute in 2003 with the objective of developing an institutional repository. The pilot project ended in 2005. DSpace@Cambridge was adopted as a strategic service to the University of Cambridge, managed jointly by Cambridge University Library and the University Computing Service on 1 July 2006. This is the archived version of the project website which was superseded by the current webpage in January 2008. </description> <dc:date>2003-01-01T00:00:00Z</dc:date> </item> <item rdf:about="http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/194744"> <title>Self-archiving and DSpace@Cambridge</title> <link>http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/194744</link> <description>Self-archiving and DSpace@Cambridge Stangeland, Elin Presentation held at Unilever Centre for Molecular Science Informatics, November 12th 2007 </description> <dc:date>2007-11-12T00:00:00Z</dc:date> </item> <item rdf:about="http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/183656"> <title>DSpace Update</title> <link>http://www.repository.cam.ac.uk:80/handle/1810/183656</link> <description>DSpace Update Downing, Jim The presentation covers some key facts about the state of the DSpace software and community in October 2006.   On the software side 1.4 has been release, 1.4.1 is coming soon and some potential features of 1.5 are described.  The development community is large and growing, having adopted an Apache project model. Some centralized organization is required; the status of the governance development process is described. </description> <dc:date>2006-10-19T11:20:58Z</dc:date> </item> </rdf:RDF>
